messages.text: Thank you for having my back at school today.
I know that wasn’t easy. Especially since we don’t even really know each other.
I guess at first I thought it was weird but I’m glad you helped.
I’m tired of those girls always talking about people.
Have they said things about you?
Listen Rose, it’s nothing, OK? You don’t have to be nice to me.
I know what everyone says about me.
Is that your way of apologizing?
I’m sorry that I’m an idiot.
It’s been nice talking to you.
No I can’t. I got to go.
I’m not trying to be. I knew since I was a kid.
Let’s say I believe you, why are you telling me?
Today I saw how strong you were against those bullies.
It inspired me. I want to be your friend. I want to be like you.
I don’t know what to say.
My first crush was Ariel from The Little Mermaid.
LOL. According to what everyone else says – that was *my* first crush.
I think I helped spread that rumor about you because I didn’t want anyone to focus on me.
Can I ask you a personal question?
I need to figure out what your life is like.
When everyone stares at me. When the girls call me weird and the boys laugh at me.
When my mother keeps asking me if everything is okay. When I cry at night because I feel alone.
What did the rose say to the daisy?
You heard about Ms. Dee deciding to make the science project mandatory?
Yeah. And I thought I almost went through all of high school without having to rely on someone else for my grade.
You want to be my partner?
I promise I’ll do my part of the work.
Less than two minutes ago I didn’t even know you.
So now I’m suppose to be your friend?
Something about it doesn’t feel right.
That’s only because you still have to get to know me.
I don’t do projects with anyone I don’t know.
Actually I don’t do anything with anyone I don’t know.
For being such a loner, you certainly were my buddy against the girls.
I’m not. I don’t need a friend.
You don’t have to be by yourself anymore.
I have an essay I have to finish. It was nice talking to you.
Answer that and I’ll leave you alone.
I’m still trying to figure that out.
Me too. So why do it alone?
I never had a friend before.
Why? Is something wrong with you?
Are you like crazy? Some kind of serial killer?
Then I don’t see what the problem is.
You’re surely being pushy about this.
What kind of question is that? Who asks that?
This is by far the most bizarre conversation I have ever had.
I promise you more to come.
And trips to the bowling alley.
And complaints about school and parents.
By the way, who at school do you think is cute?
It’s way too soon for that.
This girl in my homeroom class.
We’re in the same class. Who?
Oh. You’re going to say me, aren’t you?
What are you doing after school tomorrow?
You know, besides going home and doing all of your alone stuff.
Who cares. I don’t. Do you?
Now log off and get back to your essay.
